&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a successful candidate to make a real difference to the dental health of children in South Wales as we expand the number of consultants, specialists and specialist trainees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wales has an excellent national oral health programme (Designed to Smile) which is reducing the caries experience of children in high need areas; however, we want to do much more to improve dental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We hope to appoint a 4-session post based at the University Dental Hospital, Cardiff with potential sessions at the Children’s Hospital for Wales, treating children under general anaesthetic, and teaching undergraduate students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work closely with the already established network of enthusiastic consultants, specialists, and specialist trainees, (as well as health and social care teams) working across South Wales.&lt;/p&gt;
